# Agent System v1 (Contract-Driven Dev Pipeline)

## Objective
Stand up a contract-driven, multi-agent development system in-repo that:
- Enforces stage-gated development (Plan → Design → Build → Validate → UX → Review → Release)
- Uses structured report artifacts as handoff contracts
- Includes Business Manager + End User agents with veto authority
- Is executable by Pete with zero schema guessing and deterministic outputs

---

## Scope
IN:
- /agents role definitions (Planner, Architect, Builder, Validator, Reviewer, Ops, Business Manager, End User)
- /reports templates (PLAN_REPORT, DESIGN_REPORT, etc.)
- /prompts task playbooks for each stage
- /runbooks execution protocol (how to run a cycle)
- Sample end-to-end cycle doc

OUT:
- No UI/app build
- No DB object changes (this is process layer only)

---

## Constraints
- One logical artifact per file
- Markdown only
- No implicit contracts — everything explicit and named
- All outputs must map to a report template
- No agent can approve its own work

